quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to create a valid switch statement.
[!raw!]
int x = 33;
{0}(x) {
  case 8:
    Console.WriteLine("Value is 8");
    break;
  case 18{1}
    Console.WriteLine("Value is 18");
    break;
  {2} 33:
    Console.WriteLine("Value is 33");
    break;
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]switch[/h1]

The [b]switch [/b]statement provides a more elegant way to test a variable for equality against a list of values.
Each value is called a [b]case[/b], and the variable being switched on is checked for each switch case.
[b]For example:[/b] [code format="cs" codeId="833"]int num = 3;
[b]switch [/b](num)
{
  [b]case [/b]1:
   Console.WriteLine("one");
   break;
  [b]case [/b]2:
   Console.WriteLine("two");
   break;
  [b]case [/b]3:
   Console.WriteLine("three");
   break;
}
//Outputs "three"[/code]
Each [b]case [/b]represents a value to be checked, followed by a colon, and the statements to get executed if that case is matched.
[note]A [b]switch [/b]statement can include any number of [b]cases[/b]. However, no two case labels may contain the same constant value.
The [b]break;[/b] statement that ends each [b]case [/b]will be covered shortly.[/note]

quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to test the x variable with a switch statement.
[!raw!]
{0} (x) {
  case 10:
    Console.WriteLine("Ten");
    {1};
  case 20:
    Console.WriteLine("Twenty");
    break;
  {2}:
    Console.WriteLine("No match");.
    break;
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The default Case[/h1]

In a switch statement, the optional [b]default [/b]case is executed when none of the previous cases match.
[b]Example: [/b] [code format="cs" codeId="834"]int age = 88;
switch (age) {
  case 16:
    Console.WriteLine("Too young");
    break;
  case 42:
    Console.WriteLine("Adult");
    break;
  case 70:
    Console.WriteLine("Senior");
    break;
 [b] default:[/b]
    Console.WriteLine("The default case");
    break;
}
// Outputs "The default case"[/code]
[note]The [b]default [/b]code executes when none of the cases matches the switch expression.[/note]
